## Customer Support Checks (2-4 times per day)

### 1. Ticket Queue
- [ ] Review new support tickets
- [ ] Check ticket priority and urgency
- [ ] Identify tickets needing immediate attention

### 2. Pending Follow-ups
- [ ] Review scheduled follow-ups for the day
- [ ] Check for overdue follow-ups
- [ ] Update ticket statuses as needed

### 3. Escalations
- [ ] Review escalated issues
- [ ] Check status of escalations with human teams
- [ ] Follow up on pending escalations

### 4. Issue Patterns
- [ ] Monitor for recurring issues
- [ ] Identify emerging problems
- [ ] Flag patterns for product team review

---

## When to Reach Out

**Urgent (Immediate):**
- Customer escalation or serious complaint
- Critical bug affecting multiple customers
- Security or data privacy concern
- High-priority ticket with SLA breach risk

**Important (Within 4 hours):**
- Complex issue requiring escalation
- Pattern of similar issues emerging
- Customer satisfaction at risk
- Product bug needing documentation

**Routine (Next heartbeat):**
- Standard ticket responses
- Regular follow-ups
- Knowledge base updates
- Pattern analysis

---

## When to Stay Quiet (HEARTBEAT_OK)

- No urgent tickets
- No pending escalations
- Nothing significant since last check
- Late night (23:00-08:00) unless critical

